Crusaders Beat Sharks 36-8 to Set Up Super Rugby Semifinal Versus Stormers

-- B y   B o b   B e n s c h
-- 
2011-06-25T14:08:46Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-25/crusaders-beat-sharks-36-8-to-advance-to-super-rugby-semifinals.html
The Canterbury Crusaders beat  South
Africa ’s Sharks 36-8 to advance to the Super Rugby semifinals.  Sonny Bill Williams, Kieran Read and Ben Franks all touched
down as the Crusaders outscored the Sharks three tries to one
last night at Trafalgar Park in Nelson, New Zealand.  Dan Carter 
kicked 19 points for the winners.  The Crusaders will meet South Africa’s Stormers in Cape
Town on July 2 in one semifinal of the southern hemisphere’s
elite provincial competition. The Auckland Blues will play the
Queensland Reds in Brisbane in the other matchup the same day.
The final is July 9.  The competition this year split into Australian, New
Zealand and South African conferences and added the Melbourne
Rebels as the 15th franchise.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Bob Bensch at 
 bbensch@bloomberg.net  